I put 11% between 3,900 and 4,175, 65% between 4,175 and 4,450, 19% at 4,450 and 4,725 and 5% between 4,725 and 5,000. The reason I did all this is that currently the value is 3,873 but it has been on a downward trajectory. By late November, I figure that it should have enough time to recover and return to the mean. Also, the economy is still rebounding from covid and with more time, the value will rise. Lastly, in late November, the midterms will have recently ended and as we know, election results heavily influence the stock market.

For years the Fed has been doing low interest rates and QE in order to create a "wealth effect". The idea is that their stimulus would drive up the stock market and the value of housing and make Americans feel like they had more money to spend which would stimulate the economy. If this is true, then the reverse must be true as the FED raises interest rates and if they try to follow through with quantitative tightening (which I am skeptical they will do) then we should have a reverse wealth effect with the value of the stock market and housing declining.
